 -- Petr Krasnoshchekov <petr.krasnoshchekov@wirenboard.com>  Mon, 18 May 2026 10:39:04 +0500

wb-mqtt-dali (1.12.0) stable; urgency=medium

  * Per-control polling schedule: each readable control tracks its own
    deadline. Controls without an override fall back to the bus
    polling_interval; alarm-style controls (error_status,
    thermal_lamp_protection, thermal_gear_protection) use a fixed 120 s
    period independent of the bus default.
  * Cap each polling tick at 3 DALI commands in total (across all devices on
    the bus), so EXECUTE_CONTROL is dispatched between ticks instead of
    waiting for a full per-device round.
  * Split the DT-8 colour poll into preemptable subbatches: each goes to the
    driver as a separate send_commands (≤ 3 commands), the bus lock is no
    longer held for the whole colour read, and EXECUTE_CONTROL is processed
    between subbatches.

 -- Petr Krasnoshchekov <petr.krasnoshchekov@wirenboard.com>  Fri, 15 May 2026 10:59:42 +0500

